  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"STATUS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The legal status assigned to the insured person if proof of continued disability is not provided, resulting in the resumption of premium payments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e3c19fad0ec74d4024195693875376d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LIVING BENEFIT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"FINANCIAL"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The Living Benefit is an advance payment of up to 50% of the Death Benefit, available if the insured person has a terminal illness, capped at $100,000."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9e48b2c7f5c340d231cab1e863dc3229</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHILDREN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Children are considered as valuable family assets."&lt;SEP&gt;"Children are multiple minor individuals who may be designated as Primary or Contingent Beneficiaries."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8671bd5f2e04dc9f4cc083e33b5d5daf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8865028ed52b3b23f75c2db4581d310</data>
