  <data key="d2">chunk-e336bc3335eae1b8a9a02061f363f289</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REVOCABLE OR IRREVOCABLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ATTRIBUTE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The status of the beneficiary's designation (revocable or irrevocable) must be indicated."&lt;SEP&gt;"The status of the contingent beneficiary's designation (revocable or irrevocable) must be indicated."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-83a54997deba410d10252790d8246be0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LIFE INSURANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A financial product designed to provide a death benefit to beneficiaries, forming the foundation of a sound financial plan."&lt;SEP&gt;"A foundational component of financial planning, providing financial security to family in the event of the insured's death."&lt;SEP&gt;"A type of insurance that provides a benefit upon death."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e6240fb2796b537f797e57d0cca4a3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8671bd5f2e04dc9f4cc083e33b5d5daf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9664b19d2f37c02c2b9b34d8418fd48b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RECURRENT TOTAL DISABILITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A second period of total disability occurring within 6 months of recovery from a prior period, if caused by the same or related condition, is treated as a continuation of the original disability period."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e3c19fad0ec74d4024195693875376d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TERMINAL ILLNESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"MEDICAL CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A terminal illness is a condition with a life expectancy of 12 months or less, qualifying the insured for the Living Benefit."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9e48b2c7f5c340d231cab1e863dc3229</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PRIMARY BENEFICIARY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A Primary Beneficiary is a person designated to receive benefits upon the insured's passing, typically first in line."&lt;SEP&gt;"A primary beneficiary is the first person designated to receive insurance proceeds upon the policyholder's death."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-83a54997deba410d10252790d8246be0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8865028ed52b3b23f75c2db4581d310</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OWNER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The individual or corporate entity that holds ownership of the insurance policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The owner of the policy must sign to validate the change."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dfd5028f0b43132db8da74961939d00d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3987d1322918db88e8961dd954bc3f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VALUABLE PAPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The policy should be kept with valuable papers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7c9b2d4d50f1eb65ffb1c24f16aaff10</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IF LIVING, OTHERWISE TO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"This phrase indicates the transfer of benefits to the contingent beneficiary if the primary beneficiary is deceased."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-83a54997deba410d10252790d8246be0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TD 20-YEAR TERM LIFE INSURANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PRODUCT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A 20-year term life insurance policy for which an application has been submitted."&lt;SEP&gt;"A 20-year term life insurance policy that provides a tax-free death benefit to beneficiaries."&lt;SEP&gt;"A life insurance policy that provides coverage for 20-year terms, renewable automatically without a medical exam, until age 80."&lt;SEP&gt;"A life insurance product for which the Waiver of Premiums Benefit may be selected."&lt;SEP&gt;"A life insurance product offered by TD Insurance with a 20-year term."&lt;SEP&gt;"A life insurance product offered by TD Insurance."&lt;SEP&gt;"A life insurance product with a 20-year term, for which the applicant is applying."&lt;SEP&gt;"A term life insurance policy offered by TD Insurance with a 20-year coverage period, providing a death benefit to the designated beneficiary."&lt;SEP&gt;"A type of life insurance product offered by TD Life with a 20-year term."&lt;SEP&gt;"A type of life insurance providing coverage for 20 years, designed to protect the financial security of loved ones in the event of the policyholder’s death."&lt;SEP&gt;"TD 20-Year Term Life Insurance is a life insurance product offered by TD Life Insurance Company with a 20-year term and specific coverage details."&lt;SEP&gt;"TD 20-year Term Life insurance is a financial product that provides a tax-free lump sum benefit upon the death of the insured, helping to secure the financial future of loved ones."&lt;SEP&gt;"This is the specific insurance plan, a 20-year term life insurance policy offered by TD."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d797d61d4936328367b970f1b1a2a94b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c9b2d4d50f1eb65ffb1c24f16aaff10&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6297aea6185daf9585122e54b144c60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15042c9c78a8efe744537c5c84db0f52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e336bc3335eae1b8a9a02061f363f289&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9664b19d2f37c02c2b9b34d8418fd48b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e6240fb2796b537f797e57d0cca4a3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8671bd5f2e04dc9f4cc083e33b5d5daf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3987d1322918db88e8961dd954bc3f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;6 MONTHS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"TIME PERIOD"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The window within which a second disability must occur to be considered a continuation of the first, if caused by the same or related condition."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e3c19fad0ec74d4024195693875376d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;50% OF DEATH BENEFIT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"FINANCIAL"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The Living Benefit is up to 50% of the Death Benefit, subject to a maximum of $100,000."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9e48b2c7f5c340d231cab1e863dc3229</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONTINGENT BENEFICIARY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A Contingent Beneficiary is a person who receives benefits only if the Primary Beneficiary is unable to."&lt;SEP&gt;"A contingent beneficiary receives proceeds only if the primary beneficiary is not alive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-83a54997deba410d10252790d8246be0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8865028ed52b3b23f75c2db4581d310</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DATE SIGNED&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DATE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The date the form is signed must be recorded."&lt;SEP&gt;"The date when a signature was affixed, formatted as MM/DD/YR."&lt;SEP&gt;"The witness must also sign and date the form."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dfd5028f0b43132db8da74961939d00d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3987d1322918db88e8961dd954bc3f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEALTH QUESTION CONFIRMATION RESPONSES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"These are documents that confirm the responses provided in health-related questions during the application process. They must be reviewed for accuracy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7c9b2d4d50f1eb65ffb1c24f16aaff10</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHILD/CHILDREN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"GROUP"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Children can be designated as primary or contingent beneficiaries."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-83a54997deba410d10252790d8246be0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;123 456 789&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"IDENTIFIER"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A placeholder policy number used in the sample document."&lt;SEP&gt;"A unique number used to identify a specific policy or account."&lt;SEP&gt;"The unique policy number assigned to the TD 20-Year Term Life insurance policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"This appears to be a policy number or reference code."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dfd5028f0b43132db8da74961939d00d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c68826329db981562929b8432a5c1ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e6240fb2796b537f797e57d0cca4a3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3987d1322918db88e8961dd954bc3f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SAME OR RELATED CAUSE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CAUSE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A condition that is identical or medically connected to the original cause of total disability, which allows the second period to be treated as continuous."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e3c19fad0ec74d4024195693875376d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;$100,000&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"FINANCIAL"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The maximum amount of the Living Benefit is $100,000."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9e48b2c7f5c340d231cab1e863dc3229</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TRUSTEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A Trustee is a person appointed to manage assets or benefits on behalf of a minor beneficiary, especially when the beneficiary is a minor."&lt;SEP&gt;"A person appointed to manage benefits for a minor beneficiary; cannot sign a release of irrevocable designation before the insured's death."&lt;SEP&gt;"A trustee holds legal title to trust fund property for the benefit of another."&lt;SEP&gt;"A trustee is recommended when naming minor children as beneficiaries to manage the proceeds until they reach adulthood."&lt;SEP&gt;"The trustee manages the trust and uses the funds, but TD Life is not responsible for oversight."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dfd5028f0b43132db8da74961939d00d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c68826329db981562929b8432a5c1ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83a54997deba410d10252790d8246be0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8865028ed52b3b23f75c2db4581d310</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MM/DD/YR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"FORMAT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A date format specifying month, day, and year in numeric form."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3987d1322918db88e8961dd954bc3f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PRIVACY AGREEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A document included with the Policy Package that describes how information will be used."&lt;SEP&gt;"A legal document outlining how personal information will be handled and protected. It must be reviewed and retained."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7c9b2d4d50f1eb65ffb1c24f16aaff10&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6297aea6185daf9585122e54b144c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PAGE 2&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Page 2 of the form contains information about designating a trustee for minor children."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-83a54997deba410d10252790d8246be0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FINANCIAL SECURITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Life insurance helps ensure financial stability for dependents after the insured's death."&lt;SEP&gt;"The protection of one’s loved ones’ financial well-being in the event of death."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e6240fb2796b537f797e57d0cca4a3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9664b19d2f37c02c2b9b34d8418fd48b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;65TH BIRTHDAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"TIME POINT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The age at which premium payments for the waiver of premiums benefit cease."&lt;SEP&gt;"The benefit applies only before the insured person turns 65."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum age up to which premiums for the waiver benefit are payable, differing from the 80th birthday limit for the waiver itself."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e336bc3335eae1b8a9a02061f363f289&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e3c19fad0ec74d4024195693875376d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d797d61d4936328367b970f1b1a2a94b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADMINISTRATIVE RULES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"POLICY"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The Living Benefit payment is subject to the insurer's administrative rules in effect at the time of the request."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9e48b2c7f5c340d231cab1e863dc3229</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MINOR CHILDREN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Minor children are individuals under the age of majority who are designated as beneficiaries and require a Trustee to manage their benefits."&lt;SEP&gt;"Minor children are individuals under the age of majority who may be named as beneficiaries."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-83a54997deba410d10252790d8246be0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8865028ed52b3b23f75c2db4581d310</data>
</node>
