  <data key="d3">"TIME CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Reinstatement Effective Date is the specific date when the policy is officially restored to active status."&lt;SEP&gt;"The date on which the policy is reinstated and coverage resumes."&lt;SEP&gt;"The date when insurance is reinstated is considered for the two-year rule."&lt;SEP&gt;"The most recent reinstatement effective date is used to determine the suicide clause timeline."&lt;SEP&gt;"The reinstatement effective date is the date up to which unpaid premiums must be paid."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8236a16ecbc3d46f2cffaf18c4b6343f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb04334968af2cf23772b1234fa1ff3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e48b2c7f5c340d231cab1e863dc3229&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d797d61d4936328367b970f1b1a2a94b</data>
