<node id="&quot;PREMIUMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"FINANCIAL CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Fixed payments required for each 20-year term, guaranteed not to increase until the next renewal date."&lt;SEP&gt;"Premiums are adjusted if eligibility for a discount is lost."&lt;SEP&gt;"Premiums are fixed for each 20-year term and guaranteed not to increase during that term."&lt;SEP&gt;"Premiums are the payments required under the insurance policy. The policy waives monthly premiums when the insured person is totally disabled, up to their 80th birthday."&lt;SEP&gt;"Premiums for the waiver of premiums benefit are payable until the insured person reaches 65 years of age."&lt;SEP&gt;"The cost of insurance coverage, which is guaranteed not to increase during the 20-year term."&lt;SEP&gt;"The cost of the permanent life insurance policy depends on the type and amount of coverage selected."&lt;SEP&gt;"The periodic payments required to keep the policy active; these are guaranteed not to increase during the policy term."</data>
