<node id="&quot;TOTAL DISABILITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A state in which the policyholder is unable to perform the duties of their occupation due to illness or injury, potentially triggering the Waiver of Premium Benefit."&lt;SEP&gt;"The insured person must be totally disabled as defined in the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Total disability is defined as a condition that continues from a previous period of disability."&lt;SEP&gt;"Total disability means the insured person is wholly prevented from performing the substantial duties of their own occupation for the first two years after injury or disease onset. After two years, they must be unable to engage in any gainful occupation for which they are or may reasonably become qualified by training, education, or experience."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d797d61d4936328367b970f1b1a2a94b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e336bc3335eae1b8a9a02061f363f289&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e3c19fad0ec74d4024195693875376d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9664b19d2f37c02c2b9b34d8418fd48b</data>
</node>
