  <data key="d2">chunk-9664b19d2f37c02c2b9b34d8418fd48b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEBEC&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A province in Canada where spousal beneficiary status is automatically irrevocable unless specified otherwise."&lt;SEP&gt;"Actions in Quebec are governed by the Civil Code of Quebec."&lt;SEP&gt;"In Quebec, contingent beneficiaries are subrogated, meaning they automatically step in."&lt;SEP&gt;"In Quebec, spouses are automatically irrevocable beneficiaries unless otherwise specified."&lt;SEP&gt;"The rule about spouse beneficiary irrevocability applies only in Quebec."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dfd5028f0b43132db8da74961939d00d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c68826329db981562929b8432a5c1ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8865028ed52b3b23f75c2db4581d310&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d797d61d4936328367b970f1b1a2a94b</data>
</node>
